  "body": "### Environment information\r\n\r\n* `brownie` Version: 1.17.2\r\n* `ganache-cli` Version: 6.12.2\r\n* `solc` Version: 0.8.12\r\n* Python Version: 3.10\r\n* OS: MacOS\r\n\r\n### What was wrong?\r\n\r\nWrong output of the flattener when two files have the same name.\r\n\r\nSo basically I'm importing  the following in my code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/interfaces/IERC20.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nthis file imports another file, with the same name (`IERC20.sol`) in which the actual interface lives. You can check it out here:\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/interfaces/IERC20.sol\r\n\r\nHere's the problem - Flattener does not understand somehow that those are two separate files and I'm ending up with the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    \"IERC20.sol\": {\r\n      \"content\": \"// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\\n\\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\\n\\nimport \\\"IERC20.sol\\\";\\n\"\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the end Etherscan fails verification because it can't find \"IERC20\" symbol:\r\n\r\n```\r\nDeclarationError: Identifier not found or not unique.\r\n  --> Airdrop.sol:20:5:\r\n   |\r\n20 |     IERC20 public token\r\n   |     ^^^^^^\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nI would expect Flattener to distinguish between these two and use different file names for them, thus generating valid validation information.",
